Kleinfelder has been connecting great people to the best work since 1961. We are engineers, scientists, and construction professionals providing solutions that improve our clients’ transportation, water, energy, and other private infrastructure. As a responsive, cross-disciplinary team of bright, curious, and innovative problem-solvers, we are dedicated to doing the right thing, every day, on every project from over 60 offices in the US, Canada and Australia.

Built on a foundation of excellence, Kleinfelder is committed to client-focused solutions. Through our depth of experience and thorough understanding of environmental, regulatory, economic, and civic conditions, we identify and address challenges with innovation and common-sense. Kleinfelder’s integrated, award-winning experts collaborate with clients to meet their objectives - from project inception through design and execution. Connecting great people to the best work is our purpose – together, we deliver.


We are seeking a Mid-Level Water/Wastewater Engineer with 6-10 years of experience for our Laguna Hills, CA office.


The Engineer will participate in and contribute to a diverse range of engineering services in our dynamic environment. This is an exciting opportunity for a motivated, mid-career-level engineer seeking opportunities to support and help grow a successful water and wastewater group.

As a Mid-Level Water/Wastewater Engineer at Kleinfelder, you will help lead projects as a technical resource and mentor junior staff while gaining invaluable experience through a variety of water and wastewater projects. Many opportunities exist within Kleinfelder to diversify technical experience, build relationships, and work with professionals on a wide variety of projects all over the United States.

The candidate will contribute a multi-disciplinary perspective on water and wastewater projects (pipeline, process, reservoir, mechanical systems, collection system infrastructure, trenchless technologies, asset management, condition assessment, odor control, etc.). An entrepreneurial spirit with experience interacting with local agencies and clients is preferred. This position requires the ability to excel working in team environments.

Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
Develop technical approaches to water and wastewater infrastructure projects while adhering to national and local requirements;
Manage projects related to water and wastewater while continuously developing project management skills;
Prepare data for input into hydraulic and hydrologic modeling software using GIS, Excel, CAD, or other data processing software as well as oversee junior staff;
Constantly strive to improve technical approaches to water/wastewater infrastructure;
Help ensure staff and level of effort are deployed in an efficient, profitable manner;
Perform calculations and convey results and processes effectively;
Help lead and/or coordinate project related field reconnaissance and site work;
Take initiative in collaborating with other disciplines throughout the company to develop relationships and team to pursue high-level work;
Work in multi-disciplinary groups and convey ideas and recommendations over technical expertise boundaries
Position Competency Requirements
Bachelor’s degree (Masters preferred) from an accredited program in Civil, Environmental, or a related engineering field.
Professional Engineer (PE) in California or the ability to acquire a professional license within one year.
PMP certification is a plus.
Strong background in water/wastewater infrastructure engineering;
Experience managing projects related to water/wastewater;
Demonstrated experience with field utility investigations, feasibility studies, preliminary and final technical studies, hydraulic and hydrologic computer modeling, project permitting, cost estimating, specifications, public bidding, and construction administration.
Experience in the preparation of design plans and specifications, including cost estimating, scheduling and permitting
Proficiency in AutoCAD (Microstation is preferred in addition to AutoCAD)
Experience in using multiple types of hydraulic and hydrologic software in different water resource applications;
Ability to develop and coordinate technical proposals, write detailed scope of work, and develop detailed cost estimates and project schedules leading to quality deliverables;
Strong oral and writing skills with the ability to develop technical reports and memorandums with limited oversight;
Ability to convey results and discuss progress with clients as well as continuously developing good relationships;
Knowledge of local and national level standards relative to water and wastewater system requirements, technical studies, and design requirements.
Kleinfelder offers an excellent compensation and benefits package including medical, dental, vision, life insurance, 401(k) plan, and paid holidays.

Kleinfelder is an Equal Opportunity Employer – Minorities/Women/Disabled/Veterans (Compliant with the new VEVRAA and Section 503 rules)

